<p>If you didn&rsquo;t know, there are two methods of archiving subtrees
in Emacs&rsquo; Org-mode.</p>
<ul>
<li>Internal archiving (mark an item as ARCHIVED but keep it in the file)</li>
<li>Moving subtrees (move an item or subtree to *_archive.org file)</li>
</ul>
<p>I often use the latter but the issue here is that all my items
got disappeared from Org Agenda view when archived.</p>
<p>You can tell Org Agenda to show archived records by pressing
<code>v A</code> in <code>*Org Agenda*</code> buffer.
Notice upper-cased <code>A</code>. If you use lowercase <code>a</code> then only internally
archived records will be shown.</p>
<p>What <code>v A</code> does is it calling <code>(org-agenda-archives-mode 'files)</code>
which internally sets <code>org-agenda-archives-mode</code> variable to <code>t</code>.</p>
<p>This is what we can do in our <code>init.el</code>:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-emacs-lisp" data-lang="emacs-lisp"><span style="display:flex;"><span>(setq org-agenda-archives-mode <span style="color:#66d9ef">t</span>)
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>Done!</p>